# GitHub App private key for the self-hosted runner pool (cchifor/platform).
#
# 1. Create a GitHub App (see docs/runbooks/ci-runners.md), download its private key (.pem).
# 2. Copy this file to `github-runner.sops.yaml` and paste the key below.
# 3. Encrypt IN PLACE (the .sops.yaml rule encrypts only `github_app_private_key`):
#        SOPS_AGE_KEY_FILE=kubernetes/infra/_out/age.agekey \
#          sops --encrypt --in-place ansible/secrets/github-runner.sops.yaml
#    Verify it's encrypted (ENC[...]) BEFORE committing — never commit this key in plaintext.
#
# The App ID + installation ID are NOT secret -> set them in ansible/group_vars/github_runners.yml.
github_app_private_key: |
  -----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----
  ...paste the GitHub App .pem here...
  -----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----
